Here is an example of how you could write a Discord bot using Discord.js v14 that has a single slash command, `ban`. This code will create a bot that listens for the `ban` command and bans the specified user from the server.
```javascript
const { Client, GatewayIntentBits, SlashCommandBuilder } = require('discord.js');
const { token } = require('./config.json');

const client = new Client({
  intents: [
    GatewayIntentBits.Guilds,
    GatewayIntentBits.GuildMessages,
    GatewayIntentBits.GuildMembers,
    GatewayIntentBits.GuildBans
  ]
});

client.on('ready', () => {
  console.log(`Logged in as ${client.user.tag}!`);
});

client.on('interactionCreate', async interaction => {
  if (!interaction.isCommand()) return;

  const command = interaction.commandName;

  if (command === 'ban') {
    try {
      // Get the user to ban from the command arguments
      const user = interaction.options.getUser('user');

      // Ban the user
      await interaction.guild.bans.create(user);

      // Send a success message
      await interaction.reply({ content: `Successfully banned ${user.tag}.`, ephemeral: true });
    } catch (error) {
      console.error(error);
      await interaction.reply({ content: 'There was an error banning the user!', ephemeral: true });
    }
  }
});

client.login(token);
```

This code uses the `SlashCommandBuilder` class from the `discord.js` library to define the `ban` command. The command takes a single option, `user`, which is a user mention that specifies the user to ban.
The bot listens for interactions using the `interactionCreate` event, and if the interaction is a command, it checks the command name and executes the appropriate code.
In the case of the `ban` command, the bot gets the user to ban from the command arguments, bans the user using the `bans.create()` method, and sends a success message to the user who executed the command.
Note that in order for this code to work, you will need to have a `config.json` file in the same directory as the script that contains your Discord bot's token. You will also need to register the `ban` command with Discord using the Discord Developer Portal.
